SIMPLE: sloping
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sloping
<hw>Slop"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Inclining or inclined from the
plane of the horizon, or from a horizontal or other right line; oblique;
declivous; slanting.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Slop"ing*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>sloping</qex> land recedes into the clouds.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sloppiness</ent>⟦br⟧
